list_of_recommendation_sets.information: Studies have shown that engaging in emotional disclosure can improve cognitive changes, self-esteem, and adaptive coping strategies. This is supported by the work of Brian A. Esterling, Michael H. Antoni, Mary Ann Fletcher, Scott Margulies, and Neil Schneiderman, who found that verbal disclosure was more effective than written disclosure in reducing EBV antibody titers and improving cognitive change and self-esteem.
list_of_recommendation_sets.tip: Schedule time each day to engage in verbal disclosure of stressful events, such as talking to a trusted friend or family member about your feelings.

list_of_recommendation_sets.information: Research has shown that engaging in emotional disclosure can improve cognitive changes, self-esteem, and adaptive coping strategies. This is supported by the work of Brian A. Esterling, Michael H. Antoni, Mary Ann Fletcher, Scott Margulies, and Neil Schneiderman, who found that verbal disclosure was more effective than written disclosure in reducing EBV antibody titers and improving cognitive change and self-esteem.
list_of_recommendation_sets.tip: Write in a journal or write a letter (even if not sent) to express your emotions before bed to clear your mind and prepare for the next day.

list_of_recommendation_sets.information: Studies have shown that developing adaptive coping strategies, such as self-awareness and emotional regulation, can improve immunological control of latent viruses. This is supported by the work of Brian A. Esterling, Michael H. Antoni, Mary Ann Fletcher, Scott Margulies, and Neil Schneiderman, who found that individuals classified as repressors had higher EBV antibody titers, suggesting poorer immunological control of latent EBV.
list_of_recommendation_sets.tip: Practice self-awareness and emotional regulation by recognizing and labeling your emotions throughout the day to improve cognitive changes and immunological control.

list_of_recommendation_sets.information: Research has shown that allocating time for emotional disclosure and self-reflection can reduce stress and improve cognitive changes. This is supported by the work of Brian A. Esterling, Michael H. Antoni, Mary Ann Fletcher, Scott Margulies, and Neil Schneiderman, who found that verbal disclosure was more effective than written disclosure in reducing EBV antibody titers and improving cognitive change and self-esteem.
list_of_recommendation_sets.tip: Schedule time each week to reflect on your emotions and develop strategies to manage stress, such as meditation or deep breathing exercises.
